  "text": "Co-expression analysis of mRNAs during skeletal muscle development. Genes with parallel expression pattern are usually involved in the similar biological functions and pathways [CITATION_1] 57 . To identify key regulatory genes and compare the differences in mRNA expression during muscle development of different breeds, we performed gene expression pattern analysis using STEM software. These expression patterns are shown graphically for each breed in Figure S1 -3 for Landrace, Tongcheng and Wuzhishan pigs, respectively. The results showed that differentially expressed genes were significantly enriched in 7, 7 and 6 clusters for Landrace, Tongcheng and Wuzhishan pigs, respectively (P < 0.05).",
